description.displayText: Kim is a godsend.  She is not only our night baby nurse, also our coach and teacher.  She is truly special and anyone who hires her is lucky to have her.

description.displayText: As new parents, we were very nervous about letting a stranger watch our 3-month old baby girl. However, Kim is very professional (always on time and very polite), personable (we both share same great taste in movies... but then again, who doesn't like Marvel films??) and knowledgeable about infants (she's a newborn specialist and has already taught me a thing or two). I would definitely recommend her to our friends and family.

description.displayText: Kim is a wonderful babysitter. She was on time-a few minutes early actually-and is a very experienced nanny and baby sitter. When we first met, she asked a lot of questions about our (17-month old) son's habits and nightly routine, which to me, is a sign of someone who really cares about the child. She wanted the evening to be anxiety-free and fun for our son, and she succeeded. We will hire Kim again.

description.displayText: My husband and I hired Kim, she is an amazing person and very trustworthy. We are very happy with Kim taking care of our newborn, she's very knowledgeable and will provide everything a baby needs. Kim has been taking care of babies of all ages for a very long time and it shows with how wonderful she is with our little one. We absolutely love her and highly recommend her.

description.displayText: Kim has been taking care of my son full time since he was six months old. He absolutely adores her and I am really happy that we found her. Under her care he has made a ton of neighborhood friends and has lots of fun experiences that even I wouldn't have thought of. She takes him to multiple music classes, the museums, the zoos, and the Botanic Gardens all on the regular and needed no help from us to set up play dates (which was great because, as new parents with no other parent friends, we had no idea how to even go about finding him friends and playmates). I feel very comfortable having my son in her care and think she is ideal for new parents, as she is clearly very experienced and talented in developing, nurturing, and educating infants and toddlers.

description.displayText: Kim is fantastic with our son. She has been babysitting him once a week since he was 2 months old and I feel so relaxed and comfortable when he is in her care. She is wonderful with young babies and I can't wait to see how she interacts with our son as he continues to grow. I highly recommend her for any childcare needs.

description.displayText:
My family is so lucky to have found such a good nanny through Care.com.  Kim is not only a skilled caregiver but she is also quite a lovely person. 

Kim began working with my son when he was just a couple months old and dealing with reflux.  I am a first-time mom and needed lots of help. It was apparent from the first time Kim worked with my son that she has an innate skill for taking care of babies and wisdom that comes from 20+ years of experience.  Just yesterday she taught me about the ins and outs of strollers and the best way to keep a kid warm during an NYC winter.  I am a psychologist myself and can sense that she has an intuitive grasp of how to relate well with others (both adults and children!).  I have observed her to be very loving and caring with my son.  I also like how she applies her knowledge in a flexible and thoughtful manner.  She even volunteered to do more work around my apartment like taking out the trash and doing my son's laundry.  I highly recommend Kim!

description.displayText: Kim stepped in to help me out when I was in a last-minute childcare pinch - which also happened to be the first time I was leaving my 10-week old daughter with a non-family caregiver! Kim really helped me (a flustered & anxious first-time mom) with her calm, encouraging, and no-nonsense attitude. She showed up early and within minutes my girl was in her arms, being rocked and patted just the way she likes, and giving Kim her biggest baby smile. Kim knew all the right information to ask for, even when I wouldn't have remembered or thought to volunteer it (for example, if tap water was OK for fixing the baby's bottle) and I left for my meeting feeling very relieved.

description.displayText: Kim has worked for us for more than a year taking care of our son. She has quickly developed a wonderful rapport with him and established a consistent evening schedule for him including dinner, music, reading bath and bed. She does an excellent job of balancing providing him with a sense of comfort and confidence together with being stern and directive when needed. She is dependable, flexible and does a great job of communicating with us to make sure we are all on the same page. She is a true professional, and we would recommend her highly to anyone looking for a caring, creative and experienced caregiver.
